    </div>
    <div class="col-md-9 multiple-edit-warning">
        <div class="alert alert-warning" id="warning-e5cc908c-6c0b-4431-90f1-8de8217d490d">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.
        </div>
    </div>

        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-e5cc908c-6c0b-4431-90f1-8de8217d490d">
                Mr. Chetwynd
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-e5cc908c-6c0b-4431-90f1-8de8217d490d" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1952-02-21/debates/1cce6e4e-0bea-4957-ba3d-f7c2e042a344/Ministers(AcceptanceOfGifts)#contribution-e5cc908c-6c0b-4431-90f1-8de8217d490d">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">As my Question deals with general policy and not with the specific cases brought up yesterday, is it not very desirable that there should be a complete ban on the acceptance of gifts and services by Ministers, as it is quite impossible to decide when a Minister is placed under an obligation to a private firm?</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-e5cc908c-6c0b-4431-90f1-8de8217d490d" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1952-02-21/debates/1cce6e4e-0bea-4957-ba3d-f7c2e042a344/Ministers(AcceptanceOfGifts)#contribution-e5cc908c-6c0b-4431-90f1-8de8217d490d">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
</div>





<div class="content-item" id="contribution-ead70510-b556-4fa4-848b-7e014fd59a6f">
    <div class="col-md-9 edit-fail-error">
        <div class="alert alert-danger" id="alert-ead70510-b556-4fa4-848b-7e014fd59a6f">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-9 multiple-edit-warning">
        <div class="alert alert-warning" id="warning-ead70510-b556-4fa4-848b-7e014fd59a6f">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.
        </div>
    </div>

        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-ead70510-b556-4fa4-848b-7e014fd59a6f">
                The Prime Minister
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-ead70510-b556-4fa4-848b-7e014fd59a6f" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1952-02-21/debates/1cce6e4e-0bea-4957-ba3d-f7c2e042a344/Ministers(AcceptanceOfGifts)#contribution-ead70510-b556-4fa4-848b-7e014fd59a6f">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">I think that it would be a great mistake to try to lay down detailed rules and regulations, <span id="424" class="column-number" data-column-number="424"></span> which have not been found necessary in the past, by question and answer at this period of our discussions.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-ead70510-b556-4fa4-848b-7e014fd59a6f" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1952-02-21/debates/1cce6e4e-0bea-4957-ba3d-f7c2e042a344/Ministers(AcceptanceOfGifts)#contribution-ead70510-b556-4fa4-848b-7e014fd59a6f">
